1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 16.1-03 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the location of a district organization's endorsing caucus or an official
3 district committee or district executive committee meeting.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 16.1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Required location of district endorsing caucus or meeting of a district committee or
8 district executive committee.
9 1. A district organization entitled to endorse candidates under section 16.1 - 03 - 21 may
10 hold an endorsing caucus to endorse candidates for placement on a primary election
11 ballot under the district organization's rules and bylaws. The endorsing caucus or any
12 other meeting of the district committee or district executive committee must be held
13 within the geographical boundaries of the district organization's legislative district as
14 provided under section 54 - 03 - 01.14 .
15 2. If a district organization's legislative district is partially located within the boundaries of
16 an incorporated city in which multiple legislative districts are located, the district
17 organization shall hold the caucus or any other meeting of the district committee or
18 district executive committee within the geographical boundaries of that city.
